LAGOS – Alhaja Madina Sanusi, National Woman Leader, Asiwaju Ahmed Tinubu Support Group (AATSG), Has said that the recent rejection of the National Assembly the request of improved participation of women is another reason Nigerians must support Asiwaju Ahmed Tinubu in his bid to lead the nation. Madina spoke while briefing the press after the meeting of AATSG state woman leaders from the 36 states and the FCT at the National Secretariat Durban Street, Wuse 2, Abuja 2023: Tinubu Speaks On ‘Driving Vision’ As Next President Of… Inadequate Representation Of Women In STEM Poses Challenge To… She stressed that the AATSG, which has branches around the world was formed to give a big push for the presidential ambition of the All Progressives Congress (APC National Leader, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu. She said the APC Leader had been a big supporter of granting equal and full voice, participation and leadership opportunity to women like their male counterparts. She stressed: “Asiwaju has demonstrated through his life good governance, diplomacy and political game. He believes in gender equality and women’s Empowerment, which is evident, especially in his contribution to the achievement of the SDGs and the entire 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development, peace and security. “He has become an incredible role model for everyone and serves as an inspiration across countries, regions and generations. This incredible mentor has done his part, let’s support this eminent and progressive man, Asiwaju. “I salute the courage of our dear leaders of AATSG who are the agents of change, awe-inspiring women and men of calibre.”